01:15:00,533 --> 01:15:03,267
Okay, Natalie. Who's Natalie?

951
01:15:03,478 --> 01:15:04,693
- Natalie who?
- Why?

952
01:15:04,717 --> 01:15:06,250
Maybe I know her.

953
01:15:06,275 --> 01:15:07,775
Look. We gotta get him out of here.

954
01:15:09,033 --> 01:15:10,533
All right, all right, all right.

955
01:15:11,970 --> 01:15:13,712
A'ight, he's gotta have a car, right?

956
01:15:14,009 --> 01:15:17,453
So we take him down to his car, we tell him to get
the fuck out of town or we're gonna kill him.

957
01:15:17,478 --> 01:15:19,478
We can't walk him out of here
tied up and bleeding!

958
01:15:19,502 --> 01:15:21,377
- How the fuck did you get him up here?
- I don't know!

959
01:15:21,828 --> 01:15:23,328
You don't know.

960
01:15:26,274 --> 01:15:27,887
Yes, I do. This is not my room.

961
01:15:28,080 --> 01:15:29,907
It must be his room. Great! Let's go.

962
01:15:29,932 --> 01:15:32,210
- No no no no no no, we can't just leave him here.
- Why not?

963
01:15:32,235 --> 01:15:36,435
Because, the maid's gonna walk in.
She'll see him, call the cops. He can ID us.

964
01:15:38,422 --> 01:15:40,588
Okay. We untie him...

965
01:15:40,806 --> 01:15:43,211
We clean him up, and we march him
out of here with a gun in his back.

966
01:15:43,236 --> 01:15:44,123
A gun?

967
01:15:44,147 --> 01:15:45,647
Why would I have a gun?

968
01:15:46,658 --> 01:15:48,171
It must be his.

969
01:15:48,196 --> 01:15:50,243
I don't think they'd let
someone like me carry a gun.

970
01:15:52,392 --> 01:15:53,892
Fuckin' hope not..

971
01:16:00,486 --> 01:16:01,986
Which one?

972
01:16:05,222 --> 01:16:07,582
We should probably steal his car.
You know, teach him a lesson.

973
01:16:07,607 --> 01:16:08,827
Shut up.

974
01:16:08,851 --> 01:16:10,720
Yeah, that's alright for you to say.
-You're the one with the Jag.

975
01:16:10,745 --> 01:16:12,245
Alright, get in.

976
01:16:12,458 --> 01:16:14,184
I'm gonna ride with him.
You follow us.

977
01:16:14,209 --> 01:16:15,709
Give me your keys.

978
01:16:16,153 --> 01:16:17,653
Take your own car!

979
01:16:46,336 --> 01:16:49,191
- So, was he scared?
- Yeah. I think it was your sinister mustache.

980
01:16:49,446 --> 01:16:52,129
- Fuck you.
- You should have stolen his car.

981
01:16:52,184 --> 01:16:55,270
- Why? What's wrong with this one?
- Nothin'. You wanna trade?

982
01:16:59,140 --> 01:17:00,693
So what do you do now?

983
01:17:00,969 --> 01:17:02,969
I'm going to find out
what the fuck that was all about.

984
01:17:23,701 --> 01:17:26,221
Natalie, right?
Who the fuck is Dodd?

985
01:17:30,093 --> 01:17:32,903
- Guess I don't have to worry about him anymore.
- What the fuck have you got me into?

986
01:17:32,927 --> 01:17:34,427
Shh, come inside.

987
01:17:37,727 --> 01:17:40,234
- Who is he?!
- Calm down. Okay?

988
01:17:40,864 --> 01:17:44,652
This is my problem. You offered to help.
It has nothing to do with your investigation.

989
01:17:44,677 --> 01:17:45,660
How did you get me into this?

990
01:17:45,684 --> 01:17:48,128
You offered to help when you saw
what he did to my face.

991
01:17:48,153 --> 01:17:49,536
How do I know he did that to your face?!

992
01:17:49,560 --> 01:17:52,830
Because I came straight to you after he did it.
I showed you what he did,

993
01:17:52,855 --> 01:17:55,317
and I asked you to help me.
- Oh, and I just take your word?

994
01:17:55,341 --> 01:17:56,841
Yeah.

995
01:17:57,704 --> 01:17:59,204
Something doesn't feel right.

996
01:17:59,521 --> 01:18:02,215
I think someone's fucking with me,
trying to get me to kill the wrong guy.

997
01:18:02,240 --> 01:18:03,455
- Did you?
- What?

998
01:18:03,479 --> 01:18:04,979
Kill him?

999
01:18:05,111 --> 01:18:06,157
Of course not!

1000
01:18:06,181 --> 01:18:09,294
Hey. What..
Sit down, okay? Sit.

1001
01:18:09,325 --> 01:18:12,872
This.. has nothing to do with you.

1002
01:18:13,302 --> 01:18:15,935
You helped me out, and I'm grateful.

1003
01:18:16,285 --> 01:18:17,801
You have to burn them.

1004
01:18:20,739 --> 01:18:23,912
Leonard, you decided to help me.
Trust yourself.

1005
01:18:23,936 --> 01:18:26,204
Trust your own judgment.
You can question everything.

1006
01:18:26,229 --> 01:18:28,021
You can never know anything for sure.

1007
01:18:28,372 --> 01:18:31,728
- There are things you know for sure.
- Such as?

1008
01:18:33,153 --> 01:18:35,851
I know what that's gonna sound like
when I knock on it.

1009
01:18:36,038 --> 01:18:38,004
I know what that's gonna
feel like when I pick it up.

1010
01:18:38,443 --> 01:18:39,536
See?

1011
01:18:39,560 --> 01:18:42,684
Certainties.
It's the kind of memory you take for granted.

1012
01:18:43,700 --> 01:18:46,184
You know... I can remember so much.

1013
01:18:48,403 --> 01:18:49,903
The feel of the world...

1014
01:18:50,294 --> 01:18:51,794
and her.

1015
01:18:58,427 --> 01:18:59,927
She's gone.

1016
01:19:00,254 --> 01:19:03,892
And the present is trivia..
Which I scribble down as fucking notes!

1017
01:19:03,917 --> 01:19:06,621
Hey.. hey. Come on. Try and relax. Come on.

1018
01:19:06,646 --> 01:19:09,794
It's not easy for me to relax, you know?

1019
01:19:10,472 --> 01:19:11,982
Come on. Take your jacket off.

1020
01:19:12,989 --> 01:19:14,708
Now. Come on.

1021
01:19:16,641 --> 01:19:18,141
Hey.

1022
01:19:20,021 --> 01:19:21,521
Didn't think you were the type.

1023
01:19:30,169 --> 01:19:31,669
It's backwards.

1024
01:19:33,138 --> 01:19:34,458
Come here.

1025
01:19:34,482 --> 01:19:35,982
Come here!

1026
01:19:57,489 --> 01:19:58,989
What about here?

1027
01:20:00,896 --> 01:20:03,513
Maybe it's.. for when I find him.

1028
01:20:06,177 --> 01:20:07,880
I've lost somebody too.

1029
01:20:10,552 --> 01:20:12,052
I'm sorry.

1030
01:20:12,474 --> 01:20:14,285
His name was Jimmy.

1031
01:20:14,310 --> 01:20:15,801
What happened to him?

1032
01:20:15,825 --> 01:20:19,052
He went to meet somebody..
-He never came back.

1033
01:20:20,513 --> 01:20:23,052
- Who did he go to meet?
- A guy called Teddy.

1034
01:20:24,818 --> 01:20:28,983
- What do the police think?
- They don't look too hard for guys like Jimmy...

1035
01:20:31,185 --> 01:20:35,005
When you find this guy, this John G...

1036
01:20:36,372 --> 01:20:37,872
What are you gonna do?

1037
01:20:39,732 --> 01:20:41,232
I'm gonna kill him.

1038
01:20:43,403 --> 01:20:45,536
Maybe I can help you find him.

1039
01:20:50,536 --> 01:20:52,763
I don't even know how long she's been gone.

1040
01:20:57,380 --> 01:21:00,162
It's like I've woken up in bed
and she's not here...

1041
01:21:02,927 --> 01:21:05,015
Because she's gone to
the bathroom or something.

1042
01:21:10,232 --> 01:21:11,732
But somehow I just...

1043
01:21:13,286 --> 01:21:16,020
I just know she's never gonna come back to bed.

1044
01:21:21,896 --> 01:21:23,266
If I could just...

1045
01:21:24,107 --> 01:21:27,390
reach over and touch
her side of the bed...

1046
01:21:29,114 --> 01:21:31,169
I would know that it was cold.

1047
01:21:34,099 --> 01:21:35,599
But I can't.

1048
01:21:40,653 --> 01:21:42,747
I know I can't have her back.

1049
01:21:43,896 --> 01:21:45,925
But I don't want to wake up in the morning...

1050
01:21:45,950 --> 01:21:47,450
thinking she's still here.

1051
01:21:49,505 --> 01:21:53,457
I lie here not knowing
how long I've been alone.

1052
01:22:00,225 --> 01:22:01,725
So how...

1053
01:22:02,474 --> 01:22:04,224
How can I heal?

1054
01:22:07,169 --> 01:22:09,769
How am I supposed to heal
if I can't...

1055
01:22:10,726 --> 01:22:12,226
feel time?

1056
01:23:25,450 --> 01:23:27,710
<i>"She has also lost someone.</i>

1057
01:23:28,114 --> 01:23:29,852
<i>She will help you out of pity."</i>

1058
01:23:57,677 --> 01:23:59,177
<i>Awake.</i>

1059
01:24:00,974 --> 01:24:02,474
Where am I?

1060
01:24:06,439 --> 01:24:08,206
Somebody's bedroom.

1061
01:24:10,177 --> 01:24:11,920
It must be her room.

1062
01:24:13,466 --> 01:24:14,966
But who is she?

1063
01:24:23,732 --> 01:24:25,232
It's only me.

1064
01:24:27,755 --> 01:24:30,474
- Did you sleep okay?
- Yeah. You?

1065
01:24:32,458 --> 01:24:35,388
Oh, shit.. Shit.. I gotta be someplace.

1066
01:24:40,571 --> 01:24:42,071
It's pretty weird.

1067
01:24:42,622 --> 01:24:44,122
It's useful.

1068
01:24:44,627 --> 01:24:49,372
- You never write a phone number on your hand?
- I uhm.. I should be able to talk to my friend...

1069
01:24:50,169 --> 01:24:51,865
today about the license plate.

1070
01:24:52,364 --> 01:24:53,864
Yeah, the license plate.

1071
01:24:54,114 --> 01:24:56,200
John G.'s license plate.

1072
01:24:59,802 --> 01:25:01,872
You have it tattooed on your thigh.

1073
01:25:19,536 --> 01:25:21,036
<i>"Natalie."</i>

1074
01:25:23,693 --> 01:25:25,842
<i>"She has also lost someone.</i>

1075
01:25:26,060 --> 01:25:28,177
<i>She will help you out of pity."</i>

1076
01:25:33,345 --> 01:25:34,654
If it's registered in this state...

1077
01:25:34,678 --> 01:25:38,090
it should only take a couple seconds
to pull up his license and registration.

1078
01:25:38,115 --> 01:25:39,896
I'll call you as soon as I talk to him.

1079
01:25:39,921 --> 01:25:43,567
Do you think we could just arrange a meeting now?
I'm not too good on the phone.

1080
01:25:52,482 --> 01:25:53,982
You know.. it's great that you...

1081
01:25:55,997 --> 01:25:57,497
Well, that you're...

1082
01:25:57,958 --> 01:25:59,777
Helping me.. like this.

1083
01:26:00,325 --> 01:26:01,825
I'm helping you...

1084
01:26:02,271 --> 01:26:03,771
because you helped me.

1085
01:26:15,724 --> 01:26:17,495
So next time you see me,

1086
01:26:18,364 --> 01:26:19,864
will you remember me?

1087
01:26:36,716 --> 01:26:38,216
I think you will.

1088
01:26:40,427 --> 01:26:41,927
I'm sorry.

1089
01:26:45,068 --> 01:26:47,881
Lenny, before you go,
could I have my shirt back, please?

1090
01:27:03,717 --> 01:27:05,217
Yo, Lenny!

1091
01:27:05,621 --> 01:27:08,638
- I thought you split for good.
- Well, things change.

1092
01:27:08,661 --> 01:27:11,448
- So I see.
- My name's Teddy.

1093
01:27:11,473 --> 01:27:15,242
- I guess I've.. told you about my condition.
- Only every time I see you.

1094
01:27:15,544 --> 01:27:17,044
Come on, I'll buy you lunch.

1095
01:27:22,544 --> 01:27:24,505
Have I told you about Sammy Jankis?

1096
01:27:24,732 --> 01:27:26,872
Yeah.
I'm sick of hearing about the guy.

1097
01:27:27,732 --> 01:27:29,896
What about John G?
You think he's still here?

1098
01:27:29,927 --> 01:27:32,273
- Who?
- Johnny G., the guy you're looking for.

1099
01:27:32,298 --> 01:27:34,535
I mean, that's why you haven't left town, am I right?

1100
01:27:34,560 --> 01:27:37,928
- Maybe.
- Leonard, look. You have to be very careful.

1101
01:27:37,953 --> 01:27:39,776
- Why?
- The other day you mentioned that maybe

1102
01:27:39,801 --> 01:27:42,129
 somebody was trying to set you up...

1103
01:27:42,261 --> 01:27:43,473
Get you to kill the wrong guy.

1104
01:27:43,497 --> 01:27:46,200
Oh well, I go on facts, not
recommendations, but thank you.

1105
01:27:46,880 --> 01:27:50,155
Lenny, you can't trust a man's life
to your little notes and pictures.

1106
01:27:50,180 --> 01:27:52,949
- Why not?
- Because your notes could be unreliable.

1107
01:27:52,974 --> 01:27:53,969
Memory's unreliable.

1108
01:27:53,994 --> 01:27:55,219
- Oh, please!
- No no no, really.

1109
01:27:55,244 --> 01:27:57,058
 Memory's not perfect. 
It's not even that good.

1110
01:27:57,083 --> 01:27:58,372
Ask the police.

1111
01:27:58,396 --> 01:28:00,232
Eyewitness testimony is unreliable.

1112
01:28:00,257 --> 01:28:03,154
The cops don't catch a killer
by sitting around remembering stuff.

1113
01:28:03,179 --> 01:28:06,714
They collect facts, they make notes,
and they draw conclusions.

1114
01:28:06,739 --> 01:28:08,239
Facts, not memories.

1115
01:28:08,739 --> 01:28:11,463
That's how you investigate.
I know. It's what I used to do.

1116
01:28:11,622 --> 01:28:15,210
Look, memory can change the shape of a room.
It can change the color of a car.

1117
01:28:15,583 --> 01:28:17,208
And memories can be distorted.

1118
01:28:17,771 --> 01:28:19,905
They're just an interpretation,
they're not a record.

1119
01:28:19,930 --> 01:28:21,987
And they're irrelevant if you have the facts.

1120
01:28:22,919 --> 01:28:24,948
You really want to get this guy, don't you?

1121
01:28:25,138 --> 01:28:27,829
He killed my wife.
He took away my fucking memory.

1122
01:28:30,864 --> 01:28:32,590
He destroyed my ability to live.

1123
01:28:36,794 --> 01:28:38,294
You're living.

1124
01:28:39,403 --> 01:28:40,903
Only for revenge...

1125
01:28:41,364 --> 01:28:43,903
Then we'll get the bastard.
Where you staying?

1126
01:28:47,117 --> 01:28:48,617
Discount Inn.

1127
01:28:50,367 --> 01:28:52,113
I don't know what room.
I haven't got my key.

1128
01:28:52,138 --> 01:28:53,638
Probably left it in your room.

1129
01:29:09,146 --> 01:29:12,278
Hi. I'm checked in here,
but I think I've misplaced my key.

1130
01:29:12,536 --> 01:29:14,036
How you doing, Leonard?

1131
01:29:14,380 --> 01:29:15,880
Probably in the room, right?

1132
01:29:34,888 --> 01:29:35,934
Don't see my key anywhere.

1133
01:29:35,958 --> 01:29:37,527
Oh, shit, This is the wrong room.

1134
01:29:37,552 --> 01:29:39,958
You're in 304 now. I'm sorry.
I fucked up.

1135
01:29:40,221 --> 01:29:42,732
- This is not my room?
- No. Come on, let's go.

1136
01:29:43,489 --> 01:29:44,989
Then why is this my handwriting?

1137
01:29:49,552 --> 01:29:51,052
This <i>was</i> your room..

1138
01:29:51,083 --> 01:29:52,583
But now you're in 304.

1139
01:29:52,708 --> 01:29:54,840
- When was I in here?
- Last week.

1140
01:29:54,864 --> 01:29:57,049
But then I rented you
another room on top of it.

1141
01:29:57,320 --> 01:29:59,731
- Why?
- Business is slow, I mean, I.. I...

1142
01:29:59,756 --> 01:30:02,349
I.. I told my boss about the...
your condition and stuff...

1143
01:30:02,380 --> 01:30:04,349
and he said,
"Try and rent him another room."

1144
01:30:04,568 --> 01:30:06,878
How many rooms am I checked
into in this shit-hole?

1145
01:30:06,903 --> 01:30:08,208
<i>Just two...</i>

1146
01:30:08,232 --> 01:30:09,559
So far...

1147
01:30:09,583 --> 01:30:11,059
<i>Well...</i>

1148
01:30:11,083 --> 01:30:12,881
At least you're being honest
about ripping me off.

1149
01:30:13,161 --> 01:30:15,048
Well, you're not gonna remember anyway.

1150
01:30:15,294 --> 01:30:16,811
You don't have to be <i>that</i> honest, Burt.

1151
01:30:17,612 --> 01:30:19,112
Leonard..

1152
01:30:19,183 --> 01:30:20,886
<i>Always</i> get a receipt.

1153
01:30:21,467 --> 01:30:23,358
Oh yeah. I'm gonna write that down.

1154
01:30:26,232 --> 01:30:28,587
<i>- What time is it?</i>
- Quarter to 1:00.

1155
01:30:29,591 --> 01:30:31,091
Y...

1156
01:30:31,880 --> 01:30:33,380
Your room's...

1157
01:30:54,239 --> 01:30:57,328
<i>"Today, 1:00 p.m. Meet Natalie for info"</i>

1158
01:30:58,153 --> 01:31:01,997
<i>"She has also lost someone.
She will help you out of pity."</i>

1159
01:31:19,693 --> 01:31:21,444
- Natalie..
- You don't remember me.

1160
01:31:22,325 --> 01:31:25,568
- I'm sorry, I should have explained. I have this cond...
- You did explain, Lenny.

1161
01:31:26,146 --> 01:31:27,583
Please call me Leonard.

1162
01:31:27,607 --> 01:31:28,684
My wife called me Lenny.

1163
01:31:28,708 --> 01:31:30,129
Yeah, I know. You told me.

1164
01:31:30,153 --> 01:31:33,147
- Well, then I probably told you how much I hated it.
- Yeah.

1165
01:31:34,935 --> 01:31:36,771
Do you mind taking your glasses off?

1166
01:31:36,796 --> 01:31:38,296
It's hard for me to...

1167
01:31:39,227 --> 01:31:40,727
Thanks.

1168
01:31:41,028 --> 01:31:43,989
- So you have information for me?
- Is that what your little note says?

1169
01:31:44,232 --> 01:31:45,333
Yeah.

1170
01:31:45,357 --> 01:31:48,447
Must be tough living your life
according to a couple of scraps of paper;

1171
01:31:48,472 --> 01:31:50,516
You mix your laundry list
with your grocery list,

1172
01:31:50,541 --> 01:31:52,696
and you'll end up eating your
underwear for breakfast.

1173
01:31:53,333 --> 01:31:56,119
I guess that's why you have
those freaky tattoos.

1174
01:31:57,177 --> 01:31:59,938
Yeah, it's tough. It's almost impossible.

1175
01:32:00,935 --> 01:32:03,605
Look, I'm sorry I don't remember you.
It's nothing personal.

1176
01:32:06,505 --> 01:32:08,638
I do have information for you.

1177
01:32:09,489 --> 01:32:11,966
You gave me a license plate number.

1178
01:32:12,489 --> 01:32:14,522
Had my friend at DMV trace it.

1179
01:32:15,635 --> 01:32:17,612
Guess what name came up...

1180
01:32:18,816 --> 01:32:21,509
"John Edward Gammell". -John G.

1181
01:32:22,266 --> 01:32:23,348
Do you know him?

1182
01:32:23,372 --> 01:32:24,708
No.

1183
01:32:24,732 --> 01:32:27,698
But his face on his driver's license
looked really familiar, I think he...

1184
01:32:27,880 --> 01:32:29,797
I think he's been in the bar, maybe.

1185
01:32:29,935 --> 01:32:32,755
Here's a copy of his license,
his registration, photo and all.

1186
01:32:33,997 --> 01:32:37,224
- Are you sure you want this?
- Have I told you what this man did?

1187
01:32:37,435 --> 01:32:39,973
- Yeah.
- Well, then you shouldn't have to ask.

1188
01:32:39,997 --> 01:32:42,944
But even if you get revenge,
you're not gonna remember it.

1189
01:32:43,232 --> 01:32:45,070
You're not even gonna
know that it happened.

1190
01:32:45,095 --> 01:32:48,722
My wife deserves vengeance. Doesn't make
